Description: Foot and wall sherd of Attic black-glazed pottery stemless cup; delicate make; flaring ring foot, grooved on the outside; two slight, raised rings at junction of wall and foot; wholly glazed; on floor, zone of impressed tongues bounded by groove rings; inscription cut on underside.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of the Dioskouroi (Naukratis), Inside the temenos.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXV, no. 686)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1675)
